## limitations

- AUDOBS-0003's clone-2 (whole-pack self-consistent rebuild) attack was not completed cleanly due to a bug in this session's own forging script (a duplicate `MANIFEST.sha256` zip member), so the `verify_manifest_pack()` error path, rather than the `git status` divergence path, is what was actually observed to fire first in that specific run. The `git status` divergence was independently confirmed to exist at attack time, but the code path that would consume it was not isolated as the sole cause of rejection in that variant.
- AUDOBS-0014 and AUDOBS-0015 were adjudicated by source-reading only, exactly as in the original R002 observation; `github_bootstrap()` was not executed in this session either (no authenticated `gh` CLI in this sandbox; executing it would create real external repository/push state, outside `OBSERVE_ONLY` authority and outside this task's write scope).
- AUDOBS-0010's adjudication used a single re-run of the deterministic-rebuild reproduction in this one sandboxed environment (zlib-ng 1.3.1); no second, differently-configured environment (e.g. stock zlib) was available to directly demonstrate that a different toolchain reproduces the canonical bytes exactly, so the toolchain-dependence explanation remains inferred from indirect evidence, as in the original observation.
- This report's own commands and greps establish only the specific properties exercised; a `PASS` or a rejected attack is evidence for that property alone, not a general correctness or security guarantee.
- No attempt was made to reproduce or adjudicate any of the other fourteen R002 observations (0001, 0002, 0004‚Äì0009, 0013, 0017, 0018); they remain exactly as preserved in `operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/results/claude-second-account/`, per this task's explicit scope.

